model.description: Mean over 10s of Data Rate (expressed as packets per second, p/s) by pacman. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow/Red threasholds = 30k/300k packets/s. The Data Rate sent to InfluxDB is sent by IO_channel. To get the Data Rate for the full tile we have to sum all of the 32 IO_channels in a particular pacman. To get the 10s mean we sum all of the IO_channels over a 10 second period and then divide by 10.
model.title: Data Rate by Pacman (10s mean)

model.description: Each pacman should acknowledge reception of a 1Hz sync signal. Missing acknowledgements in particular Pacmen may indicate a problem in those pacmen. If the signal is missing from all Pacmen it may indicate a problem with the sync pulse transmission.
model.title: Sync Pulse

model.description: Voltage supplied to the Analogue side of the ADC to power chage collection signals from pixels to the chip. Acceptable range is (1.8 to 1.9V)
model.title: P$pacman: VDDA

panels.description: These boxes check to see if VDDD and IDDD are within threshold ranges. Digital voltage (VDDD) is supplied to digital side of ADC to power data transfer to and from chips. Acceptable range is (1.5 to 1.8V) for all pacmen except P5-P6 whose acceptable range is (1.1 to 1.3V) - the exception is needed because of differences between versions of the chips used (V2A versus V2B). Similarly IDDD is current supplied to the digital side. Thresholds are 350-750mA for all pacmen.
panels.title: Power Alerts: Are VDDD and IDDD within Threshold (blue "yes", red "no")

panels.description: Is the absolute value of the change in VDDD over the last hour less than 10%? Blue is yes. Red is no.  Digital voltage (VDDD) is supplied to digital side of ADC to power data transfer to and from chips.
panels.title: Power Alerts: Absolute Value (Change in VDDD over last 1h) < 10%  (blue "yes", red "no")

panels.description: Mean over 10s of data rates (expressed as packet count per second) by tile. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow/Red thresholds = 5kps / 50kps
panels.title: P$pacman: Data Rate (10s Mean) by Tile

panels.description: Green bars are centered at Pixel-level Mean ADC value, the top/bottom of the bars are at Mean +/- RMS. All values are calculated over a 10s window.  Red thresholds are < 5 or > 254. Yellow threshold is 250
panels.title: P$pacman: ADC Mean and RMS by Tile (10s Mean)

panels.description: Histogram shows distribution of Pixel-level ADC mean values over the global time window. The bucket size is 1. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. A value of 255 indicates the signal maxed out. Consistent values at 255 (or below 5) may indicate thresholds are set too high (or low) .  All mean values in this histogram are calculated over a 10s window
panels.title: P$pacman: ADC Pixel Distribution (1s Mean)

panels.description: Highest 100 pixel data packet rates (expressed as # packets per second - p/s) within a given pacman. Each value represents the  mean rate recorded over the last 30s. Yellow/Red thresholds = 1/5 p/s

The highest 100 ADC mean values recorded over the last 30s. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. A value of 255 indicates the ADC maxed out, which could mean we're missing information. This could require an expert to reset the threshold.  Yellow / Red thresholds = 250 / 254

Digital voltage supplied to digital side of ADC to power data transfer to and from chips. Acceptable range is (1.6 to 1.7V) for all pacmen except P5-P6 whose acceptable range is (1.15 to 1.25V) - the exception is needed because of differences between versions of the chips used (V2A versus V2B)
panels.title: P$pacman: VDDD

panels.description: Current supplied to digital side of ADC to power data transferred to and from the chip. Acceptable range is (400-700mA)
panels.title: P$pacman: IDDD

panels.description: Current supplied to the analogue side of the ADC to power charge collection from pixel to the chip. Acceptable range for most pacmen (150-475mA), but P5 and P6 are distinct (because of distinct models of chips/pacmen) with thresholds (60-110)
panels.title: P$pacman: IDDA
